{
  "message": "Update snapshot tests to reflect simplified stats output format\n\nUpdates all affected snapshot test expectations to match the new stats\ncommand output format that removed the \"Recent Activity\" section.\n\nChanges to stats output:\n- Removed \"Recent Activity (last 24 hours)\" section that displayed:\n  * Commits count\n  * Total Changes count\n  * Issues Created/Closed/Reopened/Updated counts\n- Stats now ends after \"Avg lead time\" line with no trailing sections\n\nThis simplification likely occurred because:\n1. The git activity metrics required git history scanning which added\n   latency and complexity\n2. The stats command should focus on issue database state rather than\n   git repository activity\n3. Separates concerns: use `git log` for git activity, `br stats` for\n   issue metrics\n\nUpdated snapshots:\n- stats_output.snap: CLI text output format\n- blocked_json_output.snap: JSON output for blocked command\n- create_json_output.snap: JSON output for create command\n- list_filtered_json_output.snap: JSON output for filtered list\n- list_json_output.snap: JSON output for list command\n- ready_json_output.snap: JSON output for ready command\n- show_json_output.snap: JSON output for show command\n- stats_json_output.snap: JSON output for stats command\n- issues_jsonl_export.snap: JSONL export format\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>",
